import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { UIStore } from "./UIStore"
import { Playground, PropsTable } from "docz"

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"ui-store"}}>{`UI Store`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"store"}}>{`Store`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"message-bars-forms-dropdown-menu"}}>{`Message Bars, Forms, Dropdown Menu`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="hr" components={components}></MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`This store is pretty straight forward. Here, functions involving the opening and closing of forms (and their types) can be accessed. `}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`There are also functions to call and kick out the message bar component used to notify users of success and failure. `}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Information from the department object is converted into clear, concise options for the dropdown menu. The dropdown menu also has some customizeability depending on whether or not the user has access to more than one department.`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
